Elizabeth Warren za ta "yi duba" a kan ta tsayawa takarar shugabancin kasa a 2020, in ji wani dan majalisar dattijan Massachusetts
Sanata Elizabeth Warren daga Massachusetts ta ce a ranar Asabar cewa za ta "duba" ko za ta iya tsayawa takarar shugaban kasa bayan zaben fidda gwani.
A wani taron da aka yi a garin Holyoke, a Massachusetts, Warren ya tabbatar da cewa zai tsaya takara.
"Lokaci ya yi da mata za su je Washington su gyara gwamnatinmu da ta lalace, kuma wannan ya hada da samun mata a kan gaba", in ji ta.
"Bayan 6 ga Nuwamba, zan yi takarar shugabancin kasa da karfin guiwa".
Warren Town Hall ya yi tir da shugaban kasa Donald Trump a lokacin, yana cewa "yana tura kasar baya".
"Ina matukar damuwa game da abin da Donald Trump ke yi wa dimokradiyyarmu", in ji ta.
Warren ya yi ta sukar Trump da kuma wanda ya nada a kotun kolin, Brett Kavanaugh.
"Tabbas, muna bukatar binciken FBI kafin mu yi zabe", Warren ya wallafa a shafinsa na Twitter a ranar Juma'a.
Wani binciken da aka fitar a ranar Alhamis ya nuna cewa yawancin masu zaben Warren ba su yarda ya kamata ya tsaya takara a zaben 2020 ba.
Wani bincike da aka yi a Jami'ar Suffolk ta Boston Globe ya nuna cewa kashi 85 cikin 100 na masu jefa kuri'a a Massachusetts sun ce bai kamata Sanata ya tsaya takara ba.
